// Field placement
=== INTRO_205 ===
# id: INTRO_205
# mode: day
~ set_header("Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa", "Monday morning")
He pauses.  Two years of training, two years of reading case files and attending seminars on [url=gloss:NYSE]NYSE[/url] classification protocols and learning to shoot at a range in Carp that the [url=gloss:Branch]Branch[/url] pretends is a conservation club.
This is what it was for.
"There's a club on Queen West," he says.
Huh, Toronto.  That's odd.  Most NYSE incidents are further north.  Also, a Toronto field placement is a plum assignment — someone more senior would surely be fighting for it.  There must be a catch.
"Members-only.  Been operating for about two years.  Called Sizzle."
He says the name without inflection, like it's a case number.
"It's a swingers club."
Ah, there it is.
* [You raise an eyebrow.] -> INTRO_210

// Swingers club
=== INTRO_210 ===
# id: INTRO_210
# mode: day
~ set_header("Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa", "Monday morning")
Another pause.  Robert is very good at pauses.  But so are you.
"The [url=gloss:Branch]Branch[/url] has been tracking anomalous reports associated with the club and its membership for the past fourteen months.  Behavioural changes in regular members — progressive, directional, consistent enough to flag [url=gloss:NYSE]NYSE[/url] classification."
He takes a sip of coffee.  Puts the mug down.
"We don't have anyone inside.  We need someone inside."
No shit, Bob.
