Robert nods once.
"Understood."
He folds the paper before you've finished the sentence and slides it back into his jacket.  He finishes his coffee in two long pulls.
"I'll redirect you to the Vandermeer file when you're back at the office.  Foreign-publication review.  Three months out, minimum."
He stands, leaves a tip that's too generous for the bill, and pays at the till.  At the door he turns.
"You did the right thing telling me now."
He doesn't wait for an answer.
* [Begin again] -> intro_end

